thread.title: ACC well represented on NFL rosters with opening weekend approaching
thread.title_full: ACC well represented on NFL rosters with opening weekend approaching

author: JOHN DELL Staff Reporter
title: ACC well represented on NFL rosters with opening weekend approaching
text:
Thanks to more schools being in the ACC – now there are 17 – there are more players with ties to the conference who are on NFL rosters.
The conference released its totals for former players in the NFL and its more than 360.
With the NFL opening on Thursday night teams got down to their 53-man playing rosters and the ACC is well represented.
Apple Podcasts| Google Podcasts| Spotify| RSS Feed| SoundStack| All Of Our Podcasts
All 17 ACC schools are represented with Clemson leading the way with 38 former players.
A total of 363 former ACC players are on the NFL’s active roster, physically unable to perform lists and practice squads, with 262 players on active 53-man rosters to start the season. Those numbers include the new ACC schools – SMU, Cal and Stanford.
Following Clemson’s conference-best 38 players, Miami and Florida State are tied for the second-most with 31 players, while Stanford has 29 players in the NFL. N.C. State and Pitt round out the top five in the conference with 28 and 27 players on NFL rosters.
